    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Strategy  <br />
It is still at 80 cards...but the good news is - YOU can use them all...so if you lose a card to discarding - it&#39;s ok.<br />
<br />
The Fellowship is meant to run...But they can fight, which is why used Valor and Strength of Arms. Plus with Gimli support, with axe and hand axe and events. He can beat just about anyone. <br />
<br />
Shadow is meant to hurt and burdenize. IF you can get enough burdens, which you can, your events become more useful. I am looking to add more Easterlings - but I am really looking for input on the Southron part of the shadow. <br />
<br />
I haven&#39;t played anyone so far that could beat it fast and hard...But I have been mixing up the starting FP...Gimli and Legolas is so far the best starting FP for this deck.  Maybe Later I will cut back on Elven stuff and add more Dwarf stuff to add Gloin.<br />
